  • Constructor Details

    • ThanksGivingAlgorithm

      public ThanksGivingAlgorithm​(double[] inEnjoy, int[] inWeight, int c, java.lang.String[] infoodList)
      The thanksgiving problem is a play on your usual knapsack problem. A knapsack problem is when you are given a list of items athey consist of profits and weight. The knapsack algorithm find you the most optimal enjoyment given the list of objects and given a total capacity. In this problem we are given an unlimited amount of items we can choose. Therefore this algorithm is an unbounded knapsack problem.
      Parameters:
      inEnjoy - is used for the list of enjoyments.
      inWeight - is used for a list of weights
      c - is the capacity
      infoodList - is the list of capacities
